Wash and dry all produce. Put @butter{3%tbsp} and @honey{1%ounce} in a #small bowl{}; let sit at room temperature. Peel @carrots{6}, then slice diagonally into ¼-inch-thick rounds and place in a #large microwave-safe bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{} and @water{2%tbsp}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}, poke a few holes in it, and set aside.

Peel and mince enough @ginger{1%thumb} to give you 2 tsp (save the rest for another use). Place in a #small pot{}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{4}; add whites to same pot and set greens aside. Zest 2 tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then halve. Add zest to #bowl{} with butter and honey. Squeeze 2 TBSP lemon juice into another small bowl.

Add a large drizzle of @olive oil{} to #pot{} with the ginger and scallion whites. Place over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until just softened, about ~{1%minute}. Add @jasmine rice{1.5%cup} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, stir, and cover. Reduce heat to low and simmer until tender, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Drain @pineapple{8%ounce}, pouring juice into bowl with lemon juice. Add fruit to pan and cook, tossing occasionally, until just browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Place in a third small bowl. Wipe out pan and heat a large drizzle of olive oil in it over medium-high heat. Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} with a paper towel. Add to pan and season with salt and pepper. Cook without flipping until browned on bottom, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Sprinkle chicken with @moo shu spice blend{3%teaspoon}, then flip. Cook until golden on other side, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pour @soy sauce{4%tablespoon}, lemon and pineapple juices, @water{1/4%cup}, and @chicken stock concentrate{2} into pan. Let reduce by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}(plain); set aside. Using a #fork{}, mash together honey and butter in bowl until smooth; season with salt and pepper. Microwave carrots until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}; toss with 1 TBSP honey butter.

Season carrots with salt and pepper. Slice chicken. Fluff rice with a fork; divide between #bowls{} or plates and arrange chicken on top. Add pineapple and carrots to the side. Top chicken with pan sauce and remaining honey butter. Garnish with scallion greens and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges for squeezing over.

> Our chefs can't get enough of pairing chicken with pineapple. One's savory and one's sweet, meaning that the duo has some sophisticated contrasts to please the adults while also being plenty fun and familiar for the kids. In these rice bowls, they're joined by other ingredients that give the whole dish a tropical feel, like ginger, honey butter carrots, and a soy-sauce-based glaze.